  "text": "The usual fixed points, obtained by setting the one-loop β-functions to zero, have T µ µ = 0 and are conformally invariant. One could hope that more general fixed points of the type (1.2) exist. However, this turns out not to be the case [CITATION_1] . Namely, one can show that if (1.2) holds, then necessarily K µ = 0, and we are back to the usual case.",
